'''Malika''' ([[Arabic]]: مللك, [[Devanagari]]: मलीका)is most commonly a name for girls in India. It is the female version of the word [[Malik]] that means "King" in [[Arabic language|Arabic]]  Thus, Malika means [[monarch|Queen]].  This terminology has been adopted into numerous other languages, including [[Persian language|Persian]], where it is pronounced "Malekeh". It is derived from the word Malak which means 'angel'.

